 A gunman has killed four people - including a judge and a witness - after going on a rampage at a Milan court .
The defendant , Claudio Giardiello , 46 , is said to have killed his lawyer Lorenzo Alberto Claris Appiani , 37 , and his co-defendant before shooting dead judge Fernando Ciampi in an act of revenge .
A fourth victim had no visible injuries and is thought to have died of a heart attack .
